an Toomer, the American pluralist and novelist of the interior life. Race, politics, and classification were their intense and troubling preoccupations in a world they did not create, would not accept, and tried to change.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aEthnicityzUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 0aRace awarenesszUnited StatesxHistoryy20th century. 7aHISTORY / United States / 20th Century.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertHarvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z978311044220540uhttps://doi.org/10.4159/9780674038059?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780674038059423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780674038059/original  a978-3-11-044220-5  Harvard University Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_HICS  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_HICS  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK